# Java 21 Rules

- Treat Java 21 as the baseline language level across all modules.
- You may use Java features available up to Java 21 when they improve clarity or safety.
- Prefer stable Java 21 features over custom utility abstractions when equivalent.
- Do not use preview or incubator features unless explicitly requested.
- Keep compatibility with configured build plugins and static analysis checks.
